# Wiki conventions

Every page in `{{VAULT_DIR}}/wiki/` follows one of four templates: **entity**, **concept**, **source**, or **synthesis**. All four require YAML frontmatter at the top.

## YAML frontmatter

### Entity page (`{{VAULT_DIR}}/wiki/entities/<Name>.md`)
```yaml
---
title: Example
type: entity
category: {{ENTITY_EXAMPLE}}          # {{ENTITY_CATEGORIES}}
tags: [tag-a, tag-b]
sources: ["[[sources/example-source]]"]
updated: {{DATE}}
---
```

Entities are *things that exist*. Includes libraries, tools, and external systems when worth tracking (use `category: tool`).

### Concept page (`{{VAULT_DIR}}/wiki/concepts/<Name>.md`)
```yaml
---
title: Example Pattern
type: concept
category: {{CONCEPT_EXAMPLE}}  # {{CONCEPT_CATEGORIES}}
tags: [core]
sources: ["[[sources/example-source]]"]
updated: {{DATE}}
---
```

Concepts are *ideas, systems, patterns*.

### Source page (`{{VAULT_DIR}}/wiki/sources/<slug>.md`)
```yaml
---
title: "Example Source Document"
type: source
raw: {{VAULT_DIR}}/raw/sources/example-source.md   # may also point to existing repo paths like docs/
ingested: {{DATE}}
tags: [source-type]
---
```

**Note**: The `raw:` field can point to either `{{VAULT_DIR}}/raw/sources/<file>` (newly added sources) OR to existing repo locations like `docs/`, `design/`, etc. No need to copy existing docs into `{{VAULT_DIR}}/raw/` just to ingest them.

### Synthesis page (`{{VAULT_DIR}}/wiki/synthesis/<slug>.md`)
```yaml
---
title: "Why X over Y"
type: synthesis
question: "Why did we choose X instead of Y?"
date: {{DATE}}
sources: ["[[sources/source-a]]", "[[sources/source-b]]"]
---
```

## Body structure

### Entity / concept
```markdown
# {{title}}

## Summary
1-3 paragraphs. Plain language, no jargon unless defined.

## Facts
- Each bullet ends with a citation `[[sources/...]]`.

## Relates to
- [[entities/...]]
- [[concepts/...]]

## Sources
- [[sources/...]]
```

### Source
```markdown
# {{title}}

## Summary
3-5 paragraphs. What the source actually says, not what we think about it.

## Key facts
- Bullets.

## Touches
- [[entities/...]] — what this source adds or changes
- [[concepts/...]] — what this source adds or changes
```

### Synthesis
```markdown
# {{title}}

## Question
The exact question being answered.

## Answer
The synthesis, with citations on every claim.

## Evidence
- [[sources/...]] — what this source contributes
```

## Link conventions
- **Internal**: `[[concepts/Example Pattern]]` — always start with the subfolder.
- **Images**: `![[raw/assets/<file>]]` — embedded via the vault's pinned attachment folder.
- **External**: standard markdown `[text](url)`.

## Contradictions
When a new source conflicts with an existing claim, add a callout to the affected page:
```markdown
> [!warning] Contradiction
> - **Old**: claim A — [[sources/old]]
> - **New**: claim B — [[sources/new]]
> Unresolved. Needs human review.
```
Do not delete or overwrite the old claim until the user resolves it.

## Slugs
- Lowercase, kebab-case.
- Drop file extensions from the slug; keep version suffixes like `-v2`.
- Example: `docs/design/example-spec-v2.md` → `{{VAULT_DIR}}/wiki/sources/example-spec-v2.md`.

## Tags (suggested starter vocabulary)
{{TAG_VOCAB}}

Extend this list as the wiki grows. Use sparingly — tags are for broad categorization, not substitutes for cross-references.

## Dataview (optional)
With the Dataview plugin enabled, auto-generate lists from frontmatter:

~~~dataview
TABLE category, updated
FROM "wiki/entities"
SORT title ASC
~~~

~~~dataview
LIST
FROM "wiki/sources"
WHERE contains(tags, "draft")
SORT ingested DESC
~~~
